parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: often requiring the driver to turn the lights off and on to restore functionality.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Deck Mounted Brake Light Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear deck mounted brake light can reduce the vehicle's visibility to other drivers, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The rear deck mounted brake light fails to illuminate or works intermittently
often requiring the driver to take the vehicle to a dealership for diagnosis and repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Headlights flicker or turn off while driving
sometimes returning to normal operation when switched off and back on. The issue can affect one or both headlights
and may occur frequently or intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The explosion of the high beam bulb can cause sudden loss of visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: High beam bulbs explode or shatter
sometimes causing the headlights to malfunction or fail.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlight assembly can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: sometimes causing the headlights to flicker or turn off.
